            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Rogo et peto primicere <note>sic</note> <lb n="2"/>tunc <note>sic</note> puellam Bariam <lb n="3"/>teretrum perdis ego <expan><abbr>Steriu</abbr><ex>s</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>modo <expan><abbr>rud</abbr><ex cert="low">i</ex></expan> cunscio <note>sic</note> me <lb n="5"/>reddere <expan><abbr>Bes</abbr><ex>sam</ex></expan> ex<supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>sium visu <lb n="6"/>peto et rogo primicere <note>sic</note> <lb n="7"/>reddas mihi teretrum <lb n="8"/><supplied reason="lost">tu</supplied>m venet Bessa volando <lb n="9"/><supplied reason="lost">Fla</supplied>ccus aliam ul<expan><ex>l</ex><abbr>am</abbr></expan> emet <lb n="10"/>et tollet mihi cor <lb n="11"/>p<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>t</abbr><ex>er</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost">Fla</supplied>ccus
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Gefunden in Wiederverwendung in der Mauer des SW-Turms des Kastells. In 2 Teile gebrochen; Inschrift geritzt; Buchstaben kursiv. Z. 3 u. 7: teretrum sonst nicht bekannt. Datierung: während des Kastellbaus 294-300 n. Chr. oder bei einer späteren Ausbesserung vermauert. (B): Popescu; Sluşanschi; AE 1981; Piso; AE 1982: Abweichungen in der Lesung / Deutung.</p>
            </div>
